4 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 7], unless the context clearly
5 indicates otherwise, the following definitions apply:
6 (1) "Farm to food bank activities" include:
7 (a) the administration of the farm to food bank program by a nongovernmental organization;
8 (b) the purchase of Montana-grown fruit, vegetables, meat, legumes, whole grains, eggs, and dairy
9 products by food hubs across the state; and
10 (c) the distribution of products purchased under this program to Montana-based food pantries.
11 (2) "Food hub" means any food pantry or food and agriculture development center that can
12 illustrate ongoing relationships with Montana-grown food producers in its region and the ability to purchase,
13 store, and distribute local products to food pantries in its area.
14 (3) (a) "Montana-grown" means an item has been grown, raised, or processed in the state.
15 (b) For the purposes of this definition:
16 (i) at least 51% of the ingredients in a processed food must have been grown, raised, or both, in
17 the state; and
18 (ii) food grown or raised in the state may be processed outside of the state in accordance with
19 existing regulations and still be considered Montana-grown.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Farm to food bank grant program -- rulemaking. (1) (a) The
22 department shall develop an open and competitive farm to food bank grant program.
23 (b) Grants must be awarded in accordance with [section 5] for farm to food bank activities.
24 (2) The department may adopt rules necessary to implement a pilot farm to food bank grant
25 program. The rules may include:
26 (a) standards for farm to food bank activities;
27 (b) methods for determining an applicant's progress in implementing farm to food bank activities;
28 (c) methods for determining compliance with the requirements of [section 5]; and
