3 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Farm to food bank grant requirements. (1) Grants awarded in
4 accordance with [sections 1 through 7] must be based on a competitive process open to applicants based on
5 an applicant's:
6 (a) ability to administer and implement farm to food bank activities;
7 (b) ability to incorporate positive change in local food purchasing;
8 (c) history of and ability to promote healthy food activities; and
9 (d) ability to demonstrate statewide relationships with food hubs.
10 (2) Applicants shall demonstrate compliance with the requirements of this section.
11 (3) Preference must be provided to applicants who demonstrate an ability to reach underserved
12 communities, especially those in rural areas and on tribal reservations.
13 (4) Food purchased for farm to food bank activities with grant funds must be food, products, or
14 ingredients that:
15 (a) are Montana-grown; and
16 (b) could reasonably be a part of an established food bank nutrition program.
17 (5) Food purchased for farm to food bank activities may not be used to supplant existing local food
18 purchases by food banks that would otherwise be purchased with existing food bank nutrition funds from other
19 sources.
20 (6) A grant recipient may spend up to 20% of the award amount on administration costs, including
21 convening and partnering with food and agriculture development centers, local producers, food pantries, and
22 food hubs.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Farm to food bank grant program special revenue account. (1) There
25 is an account in the state special revenue fund to be known as the farm to food bank grant program account.
26 (2) The purpose of the account is to:
27 (a) provide funding for farm to food bank grants awarded in accordance with [sections 1 through
28 7]; and
