8 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Farm to food bank grant program reporting requirements. (1) The
9 department shall design an evaluation report format and compile submitted evaluation reports from grant
10 recipients.
11 (2) The department shall present a biennial report, in accordance with 5-11-210, to the economic
12 affairs interim committee provided for in 5-5-223 on or before September 1 of each year preceding the
13 convening of a regular session of the legislature.
14 (3) The report must describe:
15 (a) the total dollar increase in purchases of Montana-grown fruit, vegetables, and other farm
16 products;
17 (b) the types of products purchased and the total number of businesses from which the products
18 were purchased; and
19 (c) recommendations for continuing the farm to food bank grant program.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Appropriation. There is appropriated $3 million from the general fund to
22 the department of agriculture for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for the purposes provided for in [sections
23 1 through 7].
24
